---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Personal Automation and Validation Project" sideBarActiveItemID="projects">
  <article class="grid gap-10">
    <header class="grid gap-4">
      <a class="link w-fit" href="/projects">Back to projects</a>
      <img src="/post_img.webp" alt="Project preview" class="max-h-64 w-full rounded-lg object-cover" />
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Personal automation and validation project</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-base-content/75">
          Replace this with the real project name and a concise summary once you decide which second project to present.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Project Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Explain the problem this project solves, who it was for, and why it was worth building. This is a good place to
        describe niche personal automation, system modeling, or program validation work.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Implementation</h2>
      <p>
        Add the architecture, core logic, important constraints, and any interesting technical decisions. Keep this
        factual and adjust the depth depending on whether the project is meant to impress engineers, recruiters, or
        clients.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Tools and Technologies</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-2">
        <li>Add primary language or framework</li>
        <li>Add libraries, data formats, or modeling tools</li>
        <li>Add testing, validation, or automation tools</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Links and Media</h2>
      <p>
        Add the GitHub repository, live demo, screenshots, diagrams, or example outputs here.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
